column1: Aldalómë is one of the names of the Fangorn Forest
column2: used by Treebeard in his song In The Willow-meads Of Tasarinan. The other names mentioned by Treebeard are Ambaróna and Tauremorna.

column1: J.R.R. Tolkien notes in his Unfinished index that it means tree-twilight
column2: and refers to Quenya words alda tree and lómë dimness
column5: The Lord of the Rings: A Readers Companion
